{
  "name": "AI Nodes Explained",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# 📌 AI Nodes Overview & When to Use Them\n\n## **1. AI Agent**  \nUse when AI needs to **plan and perform multiple steps**, often with tools.  \n*Example: Find the latest AI news, summarize it in Google Docs, and send by email.*\n\n\n## **2. Basic LLM Chain**  \nUse for **simple prompt-and-response** tasks with no advanced logic.  \n*Example: Translate a sentence or generate a headline.*\n\n\n## **3. Information Extractor**  \nUse to **extract structured data** from freeform text.  \n*Example: Get name, address, and product from an email.*\n\n\n## **4. Question and Answer Chain**  \nUse when you want AI to **answer based on documents**.  \n*Example: Upload a PDF and ask “What’s the revenue in Q2?”*\n\n\n## **5. Sentiment Analysis**  \nUse to **detect tone** (positive, negative, neutral) in text.  \n*Example: Analyze if customer feedback is positive or negative.*\n\n\n## **6. Summarization Chain**  \nUse to **condense long content** into a short summary.  \n*Example: Summarize a meeting or an article.*\n\n\n## **7. Text Classifier**  \nUse to **sort text into categories**.  \n*Example: Classify a message as Bug, Feature Request, or Question.*\n\n\n## **8. Evaluation**  \nUse to **check quality or correctness** of AI outputs.  \n*Example: Evaluate if a response fits the expected answer or style.*\n\n\n\n# 🧠 Quick Rule of Thumb\n\n- **Agent** → for doing multi-step actions  \n- **LLM Chain** → for basic AI prompts  \n- **Extractor / Classifier / Sentiment** → for structuring or labeling text  \n- **Summarizer** → for condensing content  \n- **Q&A Chain** → for document-based answers  \n- **Evaluation** → for measuring output quality\n",
        "height": 1344,
        "width": 576
      },
