    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# 🧠 Chat Roles: System, User & AI\n\nUnderstanding when and how to use each message type inside the **Basic LLM Chain**:\n\n\n\n## **🛠️ System**  \nUsed to **set the behavior, tone, or rules** for the AI. This runs *before* any user input is processed.  \nUse it to define how the AI should respond, what it should prioritize, or how it should behave.  \n*Example:* “You are a helpful travel assistant who answers in short, friendly sentences.”\n\n✅ Use when:  \n- You want to control the AI’s personality or format  \n- You need specific response rules (e.g. JSON output, no small talk)\n\n\n\n## **🧑 User**  \nRepresents the **actual message or input from the user** (usually dynamic). This is what the AI is responding to.  \n*Example:* “Can you find me the cheapest flight to Madrid next week?”\n\n✅ Use when:  \n- You’re passing dynamic input from a chat interface or form  \n- You want to simulate user interaction inside a static workflow\n\n\n\n## **🤖 AI**  \nRepresents **what the AI previously said** (optional). This can be useful when building multi-turn conversations or testing.  \n*Example:* “Sure! Do you have a preferred departure city?”\n\n✅ Use when:  \n- You want to provide context from a previous AI message  \n- You're chaining messages or testing dialogue memory manually\n\n",
        "height": 944,
        "width": 576,
        "color": 5
      },
